<item>
            <title>[LOG4J2-2091] Log4j respects the configured &quot;log4j2.is.webapp&quot; property</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LOG4J2-2091</link>
                <project id="12310790" key="LOG4J2">Log4j 2</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When running an application with an embedded servlet container, the configuration should be able to enable shutdown hook registration, and avoid the &quot;Log4j appears to be running in a Servlet environment, but there&apos;s no log4j-web module&quot; warning.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Steps to reproduce:&lt;br/&gt;
1. configure log4j2.is.webapp = false&lt;br/&gt;
2. Start application with a dependency on the servlet-api&lt;br/&gt;
3. &quot;Log4j appears to be running in a Servlet environment, but there&apos;s no log4j-web module available.&quot; warning is logged&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
